London Henry Maynard
S my last to you was on the 4 curitt to which referre you, sence non from you
so this to accompagine the inclosed bill for £60: att 2 uso on m Jean Savory, I say
pieter dekoker which cost Iatt 35:5 & beeng for yd acctt please to give mee creditt according
besides for the packett MN3 f the following spetia sent to Brugges to Rcoots to folloy
order

I could gett no more for the present: besides sence wee understood some news by
pray of holland out of England itt semed that the ex would fall & if itt be true
will falle much, wherefore have debained to send you more gold or remises butt
as soone wee know the certaintie shall remitt more for his acctt & continue so
that you shall finde no reason to complaind of mee, for now the spring coming
on wee shall have ooth demand & mony besides what s panishh cloathes I in ordered
would faine have some more as the inclosed pattarnes & beeng quite out of grayes
want a wole assortement of graijes, butt all lively blewish mixture no sod or
d'ull cullours amonghst them to be from 5 6 up wards to 7 6 a 8 st ayd & od
in one or other pack 2 mockes of 5ƒ6 pence ayd arthere about, besides one or
bleuw cloathes these pattarnes pray lett mij orders becarefully performed that
so noother do out sell as & that I may have assortments on his time
so shall say nomore till I heare further from you wilst I remaine
all these pattarnes are of such cullours as here
dayly are demanded, so that itt will not be amis to
governe yd self according & to buy up from bstay
to 9 st althought I want of eack cullours att least
2 peeces low prijses I say low prijses of 6 a6: 6 that
is under 7 ayd with these & formar orders you
may come to thequantitie of 70 a 80 peeces provided
you approve of itt butt severall light drap cullours
of Low prosesasone patt above N1
London Rich. Southell
In Antwerp 8 feb 1681
S. I wrott to you the 4uwitt, sence yett no news from you out of england yett
hope yd safe arrivall. I send thisday the needfull acctt S. Tonicosbt which I hope
he will finderight, sended also some patt. in case hebe in corrid gedto provided
asmall bale for an assortment, them & such like could serve you in case
any other, would make atry all althought I could wish to have some
rantie, or news, or others if any new cullours come to markett, as
desired p my last in balderston hath delivered & send meep mr. maynard
24p of blach silk hose which I have recd. butt they are extroard mary
light whoever have ordered mr. maynard to pay him the valew: now
whilst you be there if you could finde 30 orgop of modecoullours
sich woven hose itt would be well & should desire you to send them
neare to the inmlosed patt, they might come p ns mayneard
he laveing goods to send, or as you shall thinck best for us both nexd
tues day the actt of mr Himislay shall follow, from which I must
desire to inorder an assortement of grayes serges 22 yd of 36„ 34 a 3p
aps besides on assortement of modecullours y vil in all 2 bales from
mr wood of which more p next whilst I hope you shall stay mengland till
that next comes & so rest
me
En Anvers les feb 1681
Mons Jaques bassecoutt
Mons celle cy servira pour vous adviser, qui jay tirre sur vre grace cent et vinght
florins Ie die ƒ220: payable a mons. pierre meurant ce que ie vous prie de
satisfaire: I esperequ'il serat degelle bien to penfin que nous pounons vous voire
icy, estant a present bien fourm de marchandise oultre que j'ay a bruges et quil
sera qu grand leseavx seront overte, vous asseurant de linclination qusay
Mons marm Dubehout
En Anvers le 3feb 81
madr comme te temp dhiver commence ase partis et que le caresime est le
plus proche jespere qui j'aurois l'honnour de vous voire us bien top princepalen
quand les caux seront de gelld, car allors d attend be aucoup de draps et autres
manisfactures qui sont de ia arrive a Bruges, sans asso de provission que lay
encore thez moy, pour cela avec l'occasion de cette, ie nay peu pas manque
de vous presenter mon service, entre temp mons. meurant ayant laisse
chez moy de son argent j'ay prie la liberte de tirer sur vre grace trois
cent florins payable ason ordre ce que ie vous recommande de satis faire
puisque ie seray tousiours bien aises quand vous me donnerey d'occasion de
ten cormer que je suis

Brussel And. Artsens
In Antwerpen 9
mons. in antwoort vanden ul van 7 deser, bedancke ul voorde
precise betalinge aen Jff Bonnecroy, de weirde is op ul rek gestelt
ingesloten sende ul terugge den wisselbrief van ƒ 1500: tot last
francois van pruijssen geaccepteert ditto brief is seer goet kan in remise
daer voor ul dienst doen hebt maer te commandeeren den
wissel brief van d 300 pattacons will niet twijffelen oft sal
morgen betaelt worden want 25 en 10 days & beerst io fes is
soo mach ul vande weirde disponeren, en soo in casie vinde
morgen salde weird oop sicht p cas remitteeren mett voorders
ooffres mijne dinst in alle accsf
Gent Jan B Pijsbart
Antwerpen ƒ 6:18
Mons. den ul van 4 pas is tot noch toe on beantwoort gebleven nu
will hope dat de meergemelde legaturen vaerdigh sullen sijn waer van
geirne passeerde verstaen om mij volgens nae te reguleeren alsode vrind
van Englant die tot een prove geerne ten eerste saghen
